* Larry's website page on the correct tire has disappeared. It was:
http://www.roadhaus.com/Tires/Guideline.html
But in it, he said the weight rating was 1560 lbs for the correct reinforced sidewall or Commercial tire. Not
sure where you are getting the 1400 figure from.
All Larry has now on his Roadhaus website is this link:
http://www.roadhaus.com/tires.html
And if you look at the 1st tire listed, a BF Goodrich, it says Max load 1515 lbs. and then below it it says
Meets Specifications: NO

What you are confusing is total weight a tire can handle sitting still vs total weight a tire can carry while
moving.
From the NHTSA website:

Maximum Load Rating
This number indicates the maximum load in kilograms and pounds that can be carried by the tire.

Key word is "carried".
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

